<br>
My own, personal, things I look for...First and foremost, if I've been the one to throw an invitation, know they are RPers, but only because Fist of Hate is a RP guild.  I ask questions. I listen to them talk. And I WILL not invite on the fly, UNLESS, another officer tells me &quot;this person's great, but you're closer than I&quot; and then I still would go to them, and speak to them.  It's all about knowing, sort of a gut feeling about whether or not someone will fit with your guild. <p><p align="center"><a href="http://pub15.ezboard.com/bsarscorner"><b><font color="#C00000" face="Black Chancery" size="-1">Sarhea Tebaun</font></a><font
