<br>
Being made an officer of your guild means that you now have the ability to invite people to become regular members of your guild, but recruiting policy has to be a little more detailed, in my opinion, than &quot;those who can, do.&quot;  I gather your guild doesn't have any guiding policy about recruitment, which is why you brought this question here, but I'd advise that before you plan your own policies about recruiting in too much detail you discuss the issue with all the officers of your guild.  Because no matter what you may do with regards to recruiting, if the officer next to you is doing something completely different, and recruiting a completely different kind of player, you are going to have huge problems brewing beneath the surface.<br>
<br>
I can't advise you in exact detail how to go about looking for the right people, but the best advise I can give is make sure your guild has a consistent policy and everyone knows about it.<br>
<br>
Valquiss<br>
