 <p>Calonderiel Fierenduil<BR>Scout of Tunare<BR>Sentinel of the Immortal Kindred</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 302<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/25/02 10:49:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1162.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Group with them</span><hr size=1> For finding out if they're fun to play with, that's the key factor.  Every guild and every person as a bit of a different take on what makes it fun to have someone else around.  Ideally, you want people in your guild that are fun to play with and who feel the same way about you. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aradil>Aradil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 60<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/25/02 12:34:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1162.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Recruiting</span><hr size=1> I'm not an officer of a guild nor have I ever been, but I can tell you that I have become very wary of joining any guild when I haven't grouped with different members of the guild and/or attended at least one guild event to check the members out. Requiring this would also tell me that they are particular about who joins them, which is a good thing for me. I've joined guilds before (on other servers) where the officer just liked me and invited me, and they never work out. So I'm not sure if being &quot;in Crushbone looking for a certain type of person&quot; is really the best way to go for invites <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
