Wizard of the Elven Blades <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/upriestessnaeneori.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Priestess Naeneori</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/25/02 7:50:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1162.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Recruiting</span><hr size=1> I know I am new to these boards, but I am not new to EQ....I have been around for a couple days or so <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Having been an officer in a guild AND having had my own guild....I think the best way to do it is to build a reputation &amp; let people come to you. If you go looking, it makes your guild look weaker. If you are small but have a good reputation, people want to join....so you get bigger.  Most importantly....whomever you do allow in....if it so happens that a bad apple slips in...DO NOT be afraid to boot them back out.  I have seen that sort of thing destroy whole guilds before. <br>
